NOTES ON SERVICE REQUIREMENTS:

1. SERVICE REQUIREMENTS FOR CUSTODY MOTIONS (MCR 3.211):

     • A motion regarding custody or parenting time must be served on all parties at least 21 days before the hearing (unless shortened by court order).

     • Service must include:
          - The motion itself
          - A notice of hearing (date, time, location)
          - Any supporting brief or affidavit

     • Service may be made by mail, personal delivery, or electronic means (if consented to).

2. EXPEDITED/EMERGENCY HEARINGS:

     • If seeking an expedited hearing, Plaintiff must demonstrate good cause for shortening the notice period.

     • Even with expedited hearing, reasonable notice must be provided to Defendant.

3. PROOF OF SERVICE:

     • Proof of service must be filed with the Court before the hearing.

     • If service is by mail, add 3 days to the notice period (MCR 2.107(C)(3)).

     • If Defendant fails to appear after proper service, Plaintiff may proceed with hearing and request default relief.

4. SERVICE ON REPRESENTED PARTY:

     • If Defendant is represented by an attorney, service should be made on the attorney, not directly on Defendant (unless also serving Defendant with courtesy copy).

5. SERVICE METHODS:

     • Personal Service: Most reliable; use process server or sheriff
     • First Class Mail: Acceptable for non-emergency motions; add 3 days
     • Email: Only if consented to by recipient or permitted by local rule
     • E-Filing System: If court has electronic filing system, notice sent automatically

6. RETURN OF SERVICE:

     • This Certificate of Service (or Proof of Service by process server) must be filed with the Court as proof that Defendant was properly served.

     • File the return of service at least 3 days before the hearing.

